</p>
<p>Easy. Give it a try.</p>
<p>Scroll down and... hey! There it is! I can see the cool widget. And if I click...
um... if I click... then - why is nothing happening?</p>
<h2 id="html5-versus-datepicker-fight">HTML5 versus DatePicker: Fight! <a class="headerlink" href="date-picker-field#html5-versus-datepicker-fight" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>It turns out, the HTML5 date functionality from my browser is <em>fighting</em> with the
date picker. Silly kids. This doesn't happen in <em>all</em> browsers, it's actually something
special to Chrome.</p>
<p>To fix this, we need to turn <em>off</em> the HTML5 date functionality. In other words,
we want render this as a true <code>&lt;input type="text"&gt;</code> field, <em>not</em> a <code>date</code> field.</p>
<p>To do that, open the form type. There's one last option that will help us: set
<code>html5</code> to <code>false</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="d532cf8d2c">
